item.title: CVE-2019-5305|2024-08-04T19:54:53.241Z -- huawei -- mate%2010
item.description: The image processing module of some Huawei Mate 10 smartphones versions before ALP-L29 9.0.0.159(C185) has a memory double free vulnerability. An attacker tricks a user into installing a malicious application, and the application can call special API, which could trigger double free and cause a system crash.
